                "name": "Dennis Mulgannon",
                "href": "/profile/Dennis-Mulgannon"
            },
            "answer_text": "Parrots do.  It is common for parrots to bond with one particular human.  When that human is gone, they often become sad and irritable.  When their favorite returns, they will squawk or call out their favorite phrase, such as \"pretty boy\" until their human lets them out of the cage.  They also have favorite activities, such as going for car rides, and perching in the shower.  My daughter inherited our Blue Front Amazon, which is 35 years old, because when she married and moved out, he was miserable, and started picking his feathers out, he missed her so much. Over the years I have had a few parrots, and they all knew who was who in the family. ",
